The '''1954 Kentucky Wildcats football team''' represented the [[University of Kentucky]] in the [[1954 college football season]]. The team scored 151 points while allowing 125 points. This was [[Blanton Collier]]âs first season as Kentucky's head coach.
==Season== In the Border Battle, Kentucky beat [[Tennessee Volunteers football|Tennessee]] by a score of 14-13 to claim the Beer Barrel.<ref>http://mcubed.net/ncaaf/series/tn/ky.shtml</ref>
